Enable scm-cache by default.

The default scm cache properties have been configured to be 
{noformat}
plugin.bitbucket-scm-cache.eviction.trigger.free.space=6442450944
{noformat}
This property controls the threshold at which eviction is triggered in terms of free space available on disk (specifically under <Bitbucket home directory>/caches This value is in **bytes**. 

{noformat}
plugin.bitbucket-scm-cache.eviction.hysteresis=1073741824
{noformat}
When eviction is triggered the amount of disk space requested for eviction is calculated as
(eviction.hysteresis + eviction.trigger.free.space - free space under <Bitbucket home directory>/caches) This value is in **bytes**.

When disk space falls below {{noformat}}plugin.bitbucket-scm-cache.minimum.free.space{{noformat}} the scm-cache begins bypassing the cache entirely in an effort to prevent the disk from completely filling up. This behaviour can have severe consequences for the performance of hosting operations. This situation can be improved by introducing a mechanism to evict cache entries before the absolute bypass threshold is reached. Cache entries will be evicted using a LRU (least recently used) strategy. 

This change introduces two new application properties. 

{noformat}
plugin.bitbucket-scm-cache.eviction.trigger.free.space=0
{noformat}
This property controls the threshold at which eviction is triggered in terms of free space available on disk (specifically under <Bitbucket home directory>/caches This value is in **bytes**. The default value of this property is zero which means that eviction will be disabled. 

{noformat}
plugin.bitbucket-scm-cache.eviction.hysteresis=0
{noformat}
When eviction is triggered the amount of disk space requested for eviction is calculated as
(eviction.hysteresis + eviction.trigger.free.space - free space under <Bitbucket home directory>/caches) This value is in **bytes**.
